  "body": " I'm not sure if this is a hardhat problem or an ethers problem, but I it seems a bit more on hardhat side based on the error messages.  In brief, the problem is deploying with an alternate signer than account0 while at same time attaching a library in a hardhat test.\r\n\r\nSeems like I can either write:\r\n```\r\n       let factory  = await ethers.getContractFactory(\"MyContract\",  {\r\n            libraries: {\r\n                MyLibrary: libaddress\r\n            }\r\n        });\r\n```\r\nor I can write\r\n\r\n```\r\n       let factory = await ethers.getContractFactory(\"MyContract\", otherSigner);\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut I can't do both at the same time, that is include a different signer and also attach a library.\r\nIs there some obvious way?  If I write\r\n ```\r\n       let factory  = await ethers.getContractFactory(\"MyContract\",  {\r\n            libraries: {\r\n                MyLibrary: libaddress\r\n            }\r\n        }, otherSigner );\r\n```\r\nI get a weird error on the the contract name: `Argument of type 'string' is not assignable to parameter of type 'any[]'`",
